	</script><BR><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><font class="h1font">Type I: Advanced Decks</font></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr height="10"><td width="98%" bgcolor="#669933" height="10"><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="6" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td><td valign="bottom" align="right"><img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/tg.gif" width="103" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top" align="right">
<img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/bg.gif" width="92" height="24" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Your Draw</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont">Not Reviewed</font><font size=1>(13.00)</font> | <A HREF="/magic/decks/decks.php?reviews=24440">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=11683">Carl "Eol" Craig</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=11683&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck goes beserk with constant card drawing on both sides - whilst wounding your opponent and aiding yourself.  With added direct damage to tighten it up a bit.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> July 16, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> By Carl Craig<br>
<br>
BLUE:<br>
1 Windfall<br>
1 Timetwister<br>
1 Timewalk<br>
1 Ancestral Recall<br>
2 Psionic Blast<br>
1 Frantic Search<br>
1 Braingeyser<br>
1 Stroke of Genius<br>
<br>
RED:<br>
4 Lightning Bolt<br>
4 Winds of Change<br>
1 Wheel of Fortune<br>
<br>
BLACK:<br>
4 Underworld Dreams<br>
4 Dark Ritual<br>
1 Demonic Tutor<br>
1 Vampiric Tutor<br>
<br>
<br>
ARTIFACT:<br>
1 Black Vise<br>
1 Mox Emerald<br>
1 Mox Pearl<br>
1 Mox Jet<br>
1 Mox Ruby<br>
1 Mox Saphire<br>
1 Black Lotus<br>
4 Howling Mine<br>
1 Sol Ring<br>
4 Iron Maiden<br>
<br>
LAND:<br>
4 Underground Sea<br>
4 Badlands<br>
6 Swamp<br>
1 Maze of Ith<br>
1 Tolarian Academy   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck has a fun level to it, although it does really well at a competative level also - and it doesnt even require a sideboard (taking out any of the cards simply weaken its strategy!).<br>
<br>
This deck is relatively simple to play - and has a few different ways of gaining you a win, although the bulk of the damage done to your opponent will be a result of being able to do bulk draws!<br>
<br>
Its a good thing to get the likes of Underworld Dreams, Black Vice, Iron Maiden out as soon as possible, cause these will deal the bulk of the damage to your opponent.<br>
<br>
Once these are out, you simply pile on the card drawing tools like, Time Twister, Wheel of Fortune, Braingeyser, Winds of Change, Howling Mines etc... to work in conjunction with the cards listed above.<br>
<br>
There are also a few Lightning Bolts and Psionic Blasts to finish them off if need be or to pick of any early in the game creatures.<br>
<br>
The Tutors, let you seek out that Underworld Dreams you need - or the Twister, which can give you a serious advantage anytime in the game.<br>
<br>
Dark Rituals, Lotus, Moxes let you get key cards down on the table quickly - whilst the likes of Tolarian Academy let you use the likes of Stroke of Genius and Braingeyser with ease, just look at all those low cost artifacts sitting around.<br>
<br>
The best way to trial this deck (if you dont have the cards) is to simply check out Apprentice and give it a shot.  You&#39;ll come to realise how fun, original and effective this deck can be.<br>
<br>
Hope thats enough of a description to get a grip of it. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magic/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magic/decks/decks.php?reviews=24440"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24440" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magic/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font><BR></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
